Description: A streamlined approach to accessing and processing Brazilian 
    social microdata from official sources, with particular emphasis on the 
    Pesquisa Nacional por Amostra de Domicílios Contínua (PNAD Contínua). 
    Enables efficient downloading of multiple survey quarters and implements 
    rigorous panel construction methodologies (Ribas and Soares (2008) 
    <doi:10.1590/S0101-41612010000100008>) to identify and match households 
    and individuals across time. The package extends 'PNADcIBGE' functionality 
    with both basic and advanced identification algorithms, facilitating 
    longitudinal analysis of Brazil's primary labor market and socioeconomic 
    survey data collected by IBGE (Instituto Brasileiro de Geografia e 
    Estatística). Additional documentation is available at 
    the Datazoom website.
